cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper deals with traffic management of autonomous and connected ground traffic, which involves multiple agents (vehicles) interacting with each other and with the environment (intersection).
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper deals with autonomous vehicles and their coordination at intersections.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes an algorithm for traffic management, which involves control and optimization of the system (intersection traffic).
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes an algorithm that uses computational approaches to manage traffic at intersections.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper discusses the computational complexity of the proposed algorithm and its enhancements.
